title: Compare old and new driving licence categories

heading_context: Compare old and new driving licence categories
chunks.html_content:
The ‘groups’ or ‘categories’ on your full driving licence may have changed if the licence was issued before 2013.

Driving licence categories changed in January 2013 and also several times before that. Before June 1990, the types of vehicles you could drive were known as ‘groups’. These are now known as ‘categories’.

If your full driving licence was issued before January 2013, you can find the equivalent new category and check what types of vehicles you can drive.

Driving licence categories are different in Northern Ireland.

Vehicles you can drive Group before 2013 Category from 2013
Vehicles up to 3,500kg maximum authorised mass (MAM) carrying no more than 8 passengers plus driver, with trailer up to 750kg; trailer over 750kg if combined vehicle and trailer weight isn’t more than 3,500kg MAM A B
Category B vehicles with trailer when combined weight of vehicle and trailer is over 3,500kg A BE
Vehicles between 3,500kg and 7,500kg carrying no more than 8 passengers plus driver, with trailer up to 750kg A C1
Vehicles between 3,500kg and 7,500kg carrying no more than 8 passengers plus driver with trailer over 750kg, if combined vehicle and trailer weight isn’t more than 8,250kg A C1E (with restriction code 107)
Vehicles with up to 16 passenger seats plus driver, with trailer up to 750kg A D1 (with restriction code 101)
Vehicles with up to 16 passenger seats plus driver, with trailer over 750kg A D1E (with restriction codes 101, 111 and 119)
Vehicles in groups B, C, E, f, k, l and n below A See below
Group A vehicles B Above categories (with restriction code 78)
Any motor trike less than 410kg (500kg laden) C B1 (excluding quad bikes)
Motorbike D A1, A2 and A (depending on size of the motorbike)
Moped up to 50cc (max speed 50km/h) E AM, p and Q
’Invalid carriage’ (powered wheelchairs and mobility scooters) J B1 (limited to ‘invalid carriages’)

Groups f, G, H, k, l, M, n keep the same category letters.

heading_context: Compare old and new driving licence categories
Larger vehicles on a separate licence
chunks.html_content:
If you got your driving licence before June 1990 you may have had a separate licence that showed your entitlement to drive larger vehicles.

Vehicles you can drive Group before 2013 Category from 2013
Vehicle over 3,500kg with a trailer over 750kg HGV 1 CE
Vehicle over 3,500kg with a trailer up to 750kg HGV 2 or 3 C
Vehicle over 3,500kg with a trailer over 750kg HGV 2 or 3 CE (with restriction code 102)
Passenger carrying vehicle (PCV) (more than 8 passenger seats) with trailer over 750kg PSV 1 or 2 DE
PCV (more than 8 passenger seats) with trailer up to 750kg PSV 3 D
PCV (more than 8 passenger seats) and less than 5.5 metres long PSV 4 D (with restriction code 105)
Vehicles only in group HGV 1-3 HGV 1-3A C or CE (with restriction code 78)
Vehicles only in group PSV 1-4 PSV 1-4A D or DE (with restriction code 78)
